    "response_text": "The commercial opens in near darkness, with only part of a blonde woman’s face and hair visible. The image is low-lit and partially obscured.\n\nIt then cuts to a very bright, overexposed scene. A blonde woman in a pale, fluffy fur-like wrap is surrounded closely by people. Hands hold microphones toward her, and a boxy camera is visible at the side. Strong flashes or bright lights wash out her face in several frames, making details hard to see.\n\nThe sequence settles into repeated close-ups of the woman at microphones. She has styled blonde hair, heavy eye makeup, and lipstick, and she smiles and changes expression while facing the microphones and the people around her. The background remains dark, with occasional blurred lights. Several shots show a hand-held microphone coming in from the left and a fixed vertical microphone in front of her. At moments she looks down, sideways, or toward the camera; at other moments she smiles broadly. The lighting continues to flare and overexpose her face intermittently.\n\nAround the middle of the clip, the visuals become more stylized and fragmented. There are close, soft-focus shots of her face, sometimes partly covered by dark shapes or shadows. The camera appears very close, and the image alternates between dim greenish tones and bright blown-out highlights. Her face is sometimes only partly visible, with the microphones still appearing in some shots.\n\nNear the end, the woman’s image gives way to abstract, out-of-focus points of light. These bright circular lights gradually form a sign-like arrangement. The lights resolve into the word “CHEESECAKE” in large illuminated letters. Behind and around it are many thin, vertical colored streaks, like decorative light trails or streamers.\n\nThe final frames reveal this illuminated design as part of a product package. A dark rectangular box is shown against a blue background. On the package, the large word “CHEESECAKE” is clearly visible, along with a prominent “C” logo and the brand name “Cameo.” Smaller text near the logo is present but not fully legible in the sampled frames."
